---
---
<section
  data-test="comparison-section"
  class="w-full py-20 px-4"
  style="background-color:var(--surface);"
>
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4 text-center" style="color:var(--text);">
      Before vs. After RootSpec
    </h2>
    <p class="text-center mb-12 text-lg" style="color:var(--text-muted);">
      See the difference between vague AI prompts and structured spec-driven development.
    </p>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
      <!-- Before -->
      <div class="rounded-xl border overflow-hidden" style="border-color:#fca5a5;">
        <div class="px-5 py-3 font-semibold text-sm" style="background-color:#fef2f2;color:#991b1b;">
          ❌ Without RootSpec
        </div>
        <div class="p-5 font-mono text-sm space-y-2" style="background-color:var(--bg);color:var(--text-muted);">
          <p>"Build me a task manager"</p>
          <p class="text-xs opacity-60 italic">→ Agent builds 3 different variations</p>
          <p class="text-xs opacity-60 italic">→ No tests, no spec, no consistency</p>
          <p class="text-xs opacity-60 italic">→ Can't verify anything works</p>
          <p class="text-xs opacity-60 italic">→ Re-prompting loses prior context</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- After -->
      <div class="rounded-xl border overflow-hidden" style="border-color:#86efac;">
        <div class="px-5 py-3 font-semibold text-sm" style="background-color:#f0fdf4;color:#166534;">
          ✅ With RootSpec
        </div>
        <div class="p-5 font-mono text-sm space-y-2" style="background-color:var(--bg);color:var(--text);">
          <p>SEED.md → <span style="color:var(--accent);">/rs-spec</span></p>
          <p class="text-xs opacity-80">→ L1 Philosophy → L2 Truths</p>
          <p class="text-xs opacity-80">→ L3 Interactions → L4 Systems</p>
          <p class="text-xs opacity-80">→ L5 User stories with Cypress tests</p>
          <p class="text-xs opacity-80">→ Repeatable, verifiable, diff-able</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
